Question 1

library(ggplot2)
mobile_data = read.csv("mobile_data.csv")
best_company = sort(table(mobile_data$company), decreasing = TRUE)[1:20]
best_company = as.data.frame(best_company)
best_company$Var1[1]
## [1] Samsung
## 20 Levels: Samsung LG Nokia Motorola alcatel Micromax BLU Huawei ... Spice
ggplot(data = best_company, aes(x = best_company$Var1, y=best_company$Freq)) + geom_bar(stat="identity") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90)) + xlab("Company") + ylab("Counts")

mobile_lenght = mobile_data %>% group_by(year) %>% summarise(lenght = mean(dim_length,na.rm = TRUE))
ggplot(data = mobile_lenght, aes(x = year, y = lenght)) +  geom_line(na.rm = TRUE) + geom_smooth(aes(x = year, y = lenght), method = "lm", na.rm = TRUE)

mobile_breadth = mobile_data %>% group_by(year) %>% summarise(breadth = mean(dim_breadth, na.rm = TRUE))
ggplot(data = mobile_breadth, aes(x = year, y = breadth)) +  geom_line(na.rm = TRUE) + geom_smooth(aes(x = year, y = breadth), method = "lm", na.rm = TRUE)

mobile_thickness = mobile_data %>% group_by(year) %>% summarise(thickness = mean(dim_thickness, na.rm =   TRUE))
ggplot(data = mobile_thickness, aes(x = year, y = thickness)) +  geom_line(na.rm = TRUE) + geom_smooth(aes(x = year, y = thickness), method = "lm", na.rm = TRUE)

mobile_camera = mobile_data %>% group_by(year) %>% summarise(camera = mean(cam_px, na.rm = TRUE))
ggplot(data = mobile_camera, aes(x = year, y = camera)) +  geom_line(na.rm = TRUE) + geom_smooth(aes(x = year, y = camera), method = "lm", na.rm = TRUE)

Question 7

mobile_data$density = mobile_data$weight /(mobile_data$dim_breadth * mobile_data$dim_length * mobile_data$dim_thickness / 1000)
cat("Mobile with density less than water: ", nrow(filter(mobile_data, density < 1)))
## Mobile with density less than water:  1014
ggplot() + geom_point(data=mobile_data, aes(x = 1:nrow(mobile_data), y=density, color=(density < 1)), size = 0.5, na.rm = TRUE) + xlab("Mobiles")
